I was confused by the ``electrons per ADU`` units of the CCDNoise gain parameter since I normally think of an amplifier gain as output / input, so I wanted to check how the gain is actually used in the code.  I couldn't find the relevant equation anywhere in the docs, but I eventually found this in `Noise.h`:
```
        double getVariance() const 
        {
            if (_gain > 0) return (_sky_level + _read_noise*_read_noise) / _gain;
