#### Issue description

Compilation fails of the code below (gcc 6.3.1). The problem is that pybind attempts a static cast from Base* to Derived*, which is not possible due to the virtual inheritance.

#### Reproducible example code
```c++
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>
#include <memory>

struct Base : public std::enable_shared_from_this<Base> {
    virtual ~Base() {}
};
struct Derived : public virtual Base{
    virtual ~Derived() {}
};

PYBIND11_PLUGIN(foo) {
    pybind11::module m("foo", "pybind foo");
    pybind11::class_<Derived, std::shared_ptr<Derived>> (m, "Derived");
    return m.ptr();
}

```
 #### Suggested fix
Use dynamic_cast instead of static_cast in init_holder_helper().

```diff
diff --git a/include/pybind11/pybind11.h b/include/pybind11/pybind11.h
index 098d7e0..560ac07 100644
--- a/include/pybind11/pybind11.h
+++ b/include/pybind11/pybind11.h
@@ -1119,7 +1119,7 @@ private:
     template <typename T>
     static void init_holder_helper(instance_type *inst, const holder_type * /* unused */, const std::enable_shared_from_this<T> * /* dummy */) {
         try {
-            new (&inst->holder) holder_type(std::static_pointer_cast<typename holder_type::element_type>(inst->value->shared_from_this()));
+            new (&inst->holder) holder_type(std::dynamic_pointer_cast<typename holder_type::element_type>(inst->value->shared_from_this()));
             inst->holder_constructed = true;
         } catch (const std::bad_weak_ptr &) {
             if (inst->owned) {

```

